observations.recommendation:
1.15 We recommended and Management agreed to:
1.15.1 Strictly follow the guidelines and procedures in the conduct of physical count of PPE, Recognition of PPE items found at station, and disposition of inexistent/missing PPE items and require the Accountant and Property Officer to reconcile their records based on the results of the actual physical inventory and effect necessary adjustments;
1.15.2 Adopt the uniform numbering system for property numbers of PPE and require the Property Unit to update the property stickers based on the prescribed format and to include the required information under Section 5.6 and 5.7 of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
1.15.3 Submit the approved PIP to the COA Audit Team within the prescribed period;
1.15.4 Conduct the required preliminary activities prior to inventory taking; and
1.15.5 Record / document the physical count daily in a standard ICF prescribed in Annex A of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020.

We recommended that Management:
a) Incorporate the purchase of water meters and fittings in the regular budget of the Waterworks System and follow the standard procurement procedures mandated under R.A. 9184;
b) Maintain adequate levels of stock so as to ensure the availability as the need arises and to institute the proper monitoring and controls for the inventory keeping, utilization and reporting of said items;
c) Ensure that a duly authorized ordinance has been passed to cover the operations of the Waterworks System, including the policies and guidelines to ensure that both the interests of the government and the consumers are equally protected.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant should: 
 consolidate the determined cash lost due to the initial request for relief and revise the request for relief from accountability reflecting the specific amounts;
 exhaust all means to support the request with available documents to prove the veracity of the relief being sought, including the submission of the bank reconciliation statement (BRS) showing the discrepancy and the BRS of the period immediately preceding it, together with the required supporting documents.
